      "text": [
        " الدِّينِ مِنْ حَرَجٍ"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.ammaar-muslim": [
          "6. [6/-] al-Tahdhib: al-Mufid from Ahmad b. Muhammad from his father from al-Husayn b. al-Hasan b. Aban from al-Husayn b. Said from Ibn Abi Umayr from Ibn Udhayna from al-Fudhayl who said: Abu Abdillah عليه السلام was asked about the one in the state of Janaba who is bathing so [some of the used water] sprays off the ground and into the utensil, he said: there is no harm – this is covered by what Allāh the Exalted said: “He has not placed upon you in the religion any difficulty” <a href=\"/books/quran:22#h78\">[22:78]</a>."
        ]
      }
    },
